{"word":"ἐξεῖπον","slug":"ἐξεῖπον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξεῖπον</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>-ειπεῖν</el>) (aor2 in use of <el>ἐξαγορεύω, ἐξερέω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:quod vide'>q. <a href='S:vide'>v.</a></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to speak out, tell out, declare</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>effari</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to tell</i> something <i>of</i> a person, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}